Michael Olsen, 52, was jailed for 12 years after shooting a police officer in the hand in October last year . 
  PC Mark Bird was attending a routine traffic accident with colleague PC Robert Wilson . 
  Olsen had abandoned his car in the middle of the road and was pursued by the officers . 
  He turned round and pulled a gun to PC Wilson's head . 
  PC Bird lunged at him to save his colleague but he was shot in hand . 
  Olsen threatened to blow the officer's head off as he was tackled . 
  He was jailed at Inner London Crown Court . 
 